Privacy Policy

Effective Date: February 19, 2026

Home Stock Shop (“the App”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what data is used, how it is used, and your choices.

Information We Collect

1. Information you provide in the App
The App stores content you create, such as:
- Item names, quantities, categories, notes, and settings
- Shopping list entries
- Report and usage history generated from your inventory activity

2. Device and app data for ads
If you use the free version, the App uses Google Mobile Ads SDK to display banner ads.
Ad providers may collect certain technical data (such as device information, IP-based location, and advertising identifiers) to deliver and measure ads, subject to your device settings and consent choices.

3. Purchases and subscriptions
If you subscribe to remove ads, payment processing is handled by Apple through the App Store.
We do not receive your full payment card details.

How Your Data Is Used

- To provide core inventory, shopping, and reporting features
- To sync your data across your Apple devices (when iCloud is enabled)
- To show ads in the free version
- To manage premium entitlement status (ad removal subscription)

Tracking and Consent

Where required, the App may request tracking permission via Apple’s App Tracking Transparency prompt.
You can change tracking permissions anytime in iOS Settings.

Data Storage and Sync

- App data is stored on your device.
- If iCloud sync is enabled on your device, your app data may also be stored in your iCloud account through Apple’s services.

Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal information.
We share data only as needed with service providers that power core functionality:
- Apple (App Store purchases, iCloud sync)
- Google (ad delivery and measurement in the free version)

Children’s Privacy

The App is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

Data Security

We use Apple platform protections and system frameworks to help protect your data.
No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.

Your Choices

- You can stop using the App at any time.
- You can delete app data in the App or by uninstalling the App.
- You can manage/cancel subscriptions in your Apple ID subscription settings.
- You can control ad tracking permissions in iOS Settings.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this policy from time to time.
If we make changes, we will update the effective date above.

Contact

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:
betaniagpt@gmail.com
